issue.body:
**RKE version:** 1.4.3

**Docker version: (`docker version`,`docker info` preferred)** 20.10.14

**Operating system and kernel: (`cat /etc/os-release`, `uname -r` preferred)** RedHat Enterprise Linux 8.6

**Type/provider of hosts: (VirtualBox/Bare-metal/AWS/GCE/DO)** Bare-metal

**cluster.yml file:** NA (cluster created by terraform provider)

**Steps to Reproduce:**

1. Create RKE cluster either cli or terraform provider 1.23.6-rancher1-1
2. Upgrade the cluster to 1.23.10-rancher1-1
3. Erorr observed: 
```shell
"Can't start Docker container [kube-controller-manager] on host [10.148.20.209]: Error response from daemon: get 5c876d375046f4aad9745a621ab5b38b6b78141b79baeff1c23af472d95a2848: no such volume"

"Failed to upgrade hosts: 10.148.20.209 with error [Failed to start [kube-controller-manager] container on host [10.148.20.209]: Error response from daemon: get 5c876d375046f4aad9745a621ab5b38b6b78141b79baeff1c23af472d95a2848: no such volume]"
```

**Root cause:**
In this method - https://github.com/rancher/rke/blob/v1.4.3/services/controlplane.go#L321
```go
if err := runSidekick(ctx, host, prsMap, processMap[SidekickContainerName], k8sVersion); err != nil {
	return err
}
// run kubeapi
if err := runKubeAPI(ctx, host, localConnDialerFactory, prsMap, processMap[KubeAPIContainerName], alpineImage, certMap, k8sVersion); err != nil {
	return err
}
// run kubecontroller
if err := runKubeController(ctx, host, localConnDialerFactory, prsMap, processMap[KubeControllerContainerName], alpineImage, k8sVersion); err != nil {
	return err
}
// run scheduler
return runScheduler(ctx, host, localConnDialerFactory, prsMap, processMap[SchedulerContainerName], alpineImage, k8sVersion)
```
The Sidekick container is deleted and re-created with new rke-tools version. This deletes the existing volume shared by `kubelet`, `kube-controller-manager`, `kube-proxy` and `kube-scheduler`

https://github.com/rancher/rke/blob/release/v1.4.3/docker/docker.go#L370

After this the `kube-apiserver` is upgraded. But before the `kube-controller-manager` is upgraded it goes in error state (probably because of `kube-apiserver`) and tries to restart. However it fails to restart since the volume from the earlier sidekick container is gone.

Seeing the container stopped, this code - https://github.com/rancher/rke/blob/v1.4.3/docker/docker.go#L99

bypasses all conditions for upgrade

```go
// Check for upgrades
if container.State.Running {
	// check if container is in a restarting loop
	if container.State.Restarting {
		logrus.Debugf("[%s] Container [%s] is in a restarting loop [%s]", plane, containerName, hostname)
		err = RestartContainer(ctx, dClient, hostname, containerName)
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
	}
	logrus.Debugf("[%s] Container [%s] is already running on host [%s]", plane, containerName, hostname)
	isUpgradable, err := IsContainerUpgradable(ctx, dClient, imageCfg, hostCfg, containerName, hostname, plane)
	if err != nil {
		return err
	}
	if isUpgradable {
		return DoRollingUpdateContainer(ctx, dClient, imageCfg, hostCfg, containerName, hostname, plane, prsMap)
	}
	return nil
}

// start if not running
logrus.Infof("[%s] Starting stopped container [%s] on host [%s]", plane, containerName, hostname)
if err := StartContainer(ctx, dClient, hostname, containerName); err != nil {
	return fmt.Errorf("Failed to start [%s] container on host [%s]: %v", containerName, hostname, err)
}
```

 and simply tries to start the stopped container (old version) giving this error since the volume is gone.


**Possible solutions:**

The container should upgrade even if it is stopped.
Not force delete the sidekick container's volume
